{"title_page": "North East 2", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2015}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2015}}\n{{ Infobox rugby league cup\n| title          = North East 2\n| logo           = England Rugby text logo.svg\n| sport          = Rugby Union \n| founded =1987\n| folded= 2000\n| country    =  {{ENG}}\n| teams      =  \n|  website    = [http://clubs.rfu.com/Fixtures/MatchByDivision.aspx?DivID=159357770  clubs.rfu.com]\n}}\n\n'''North East 2''' (not to be confused with [[North 2 East]]) was an [[England|English]] [[Rugby Union]] league was at the eighth tier of the domestic competition when it was founded in 1987 and was available to teams in [[North East England]].  Promoted teams moved up to [[North East 1]] while relegated teams dropped to [[Durham/Northumberland 1]] and latterly [[North East 3]].  The division was abolished at the end of the 1999-2000 season due to [[Rugby Football Union|RFU]] restructuring with teams being transferred to regional leagues such as [[Yorkshire 1]] or [[Durham/Northumberland 1]].\n\n==Original teams==\nWhen league rugby began in 1987 this division contained the following teams:\n\n*[[Barnsley RUFC|Barnsley]]\n*[[Beverley RUFC|Beverley]]\n*[[Novocastrians Rugby Football Club|Novocastrians]]\n*[[Newcastle University]]\n*Old Hymerians\n*[[Pocklington RUFC|Pocklington]] \n*[[Pontefract RUFC|Pontefract]]\n*[[Ryton RFC|Ryton]]\n*[[Selby RUFC|Selby]]\n*[[Stockton RFC|Stockton]]\n*[[York RUFC|York]]\n\n\n==North East 2 Honours==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: left;\"\n|-\n|colspan=\"11\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\"|<!--\n-->\n{| border=\"0\" style=\"width:100%;\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n|-\n|  style=\"width:20%; border:0;\"|\n| style=\"border:0;\"|'''North East 2 Honours'''\n|  style=\"width:20%; border:0;\"|\n|}\n|-\n!  style=\"background:#efefef; width:70px;\"|Season\n!  style=\"background:#efefef; width:50px;\"|No of Teams\n!  style=\"background:#efefef; width:175px;\"|Champions\n!  style=\"