 was at the eighth tier of the domestic competition when it was founded in 1987 and was available to teams in [[North East England]].  Promoted teams moved up to [[North East 1]] while relegated teams dropped to [[Durham/Northumberland 1]] and latterly [[North East 3]].  The division was abolished at the end of the 1999-00 season due to [[Rugby Football Union|RFU]] restructuring with teams being transferred to regional leagues such as [[Yorkshire 1]] or [[Durham/Northumberland 1]].\n\n==Original teams==\nWhen league rugby began in 1987 this division contained the following teams:\n\n*[[Barnsley RUFC|Barnsley]]\n*[[Beverley RUFC|Beverley]]\n*[[Novocastrians Rugby Football Club|Novocastrians]]\n*[[Newcastle University]]\n*Old Hymerians\n*[[Pocklington RUFC|Pocklington]] \n*[[Pontefract RUFC|Pontefract]]\n*[[Ryton RFC|Ryton]]\n*[[Selby RUFC|Selby]]\n*[[Stockton RFC|Stockton]]\n*[[York RUFC|York]]\n\n\n==North East 2 Honours==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: left;\"\n|-\n|colspan=\"11\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\"|<!--\n-->\n{| border=\"0\" style=\"width:100%;\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\"\n|-\n|  style=\"width:20%; border:0;\"|\n| style=\"border:0;\"|'''North East 2 Honours'''\n|  style=\"width:20%; border:0;\"|\n|}\n|-\n!  style=\"background:#efefef; width:70px;\"|Season\n!  style=\"background:#efefef; width:50px;\"|No of Teams\n!  style=\"background:#efefef; width:175px;\"|Champions\n!  style=\"background:#efefef; width:175px;\"|Runners\u2013up\n!  style=\"background:#efefef; width:300px;\"|Relegated Teams\n!  style=\"background:#efefef; width:200px;\"|League Name\n|- align=left\n| 1987-88 || 11 || style=\"background:#d8ffeb;\"| '''[[Novocastrians Rugby Football Club|Novocastrians]]''' || style=\"background:#d8ffeb;\"|[[Stockton RFC|Stockton]]||[[Barnsley RUFC|Barnsley]]|| North East 2 \n|-\n| 1988-89 || 11 || style=\"background:#d8ffeb;\"| '''[[York RUFC|York]]''' || style=\"background:#d8ffeb;\"| [[Selby RUFC|Selby]]|| [[Pocklington RUFC